<subSubSection id="18D9651C6451FF99FF0DFB30F1323C78" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="507C36976451FF99FF0DFB30F1323C78" blockId="3.[151,1437,258,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FF0DFB30F3603C5C" bold="true" box="[199,334,1266,1291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the native “ 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FCDCFB30F17B3C5C" box="[790,853,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" status="sp. nov.">Puris</taxonomicName>
”, who lived in the Paraíba river area, near Serra da Mantiqueira, where is located the municipality of Itatiaia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="18D9651C6451FF9FFF0DFAF8F00639AF" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="507C36976451FF99FF0DFAF8F6503F18" blockId="3.[151,1437,258,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FF0DFAF8F3153C04" bold="true" box="[199,315,1338,1363]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">Remarks.</emphasis>
Both the new species are similar to each other in general shape of the body, general pattern of setae, maculae and bands, form and pattern of interstriae. In contrast, they differ from each other by the colour and reflections on head, pronotum (
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FDC9FA40F07D3CCC" box="[515,595,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1984]" captionTargetBox="[170,1422,276,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,267,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Conognatha (Pithiscus) coffeatus Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1 and 3, habitus; 2, lateral view; 4, frontal view of head; 5, ventral view of antennae; 6, shape of pronotum; 7, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224727/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Figs. 
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FD8FFA41F07D3CCC" box="[581,595,1411,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FD5AFA41F0B13CCC" box="[656,671,1411,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1430,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 8 and 10, habitus; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FD5AFA41F0B13CCC" box="[656,671,1411,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
), ventral surface and legs, by the presence of a short longitudinal groove between the vertex and the frons in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FDB5FA65F1273CE9" box="[639,777,1447,1470]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FDB5FA65F1273CE9" box="[639,777,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
