), shape of the frons rectangular in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FA9EFA65F2D23CB4" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FA9EFA65F2D23CB4" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="798457FE6451FF99FECEFA08F3703CB4" box="[260,350,1482,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" rank="species">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FECEFA08F3703CB4" bold="true" box="[260,350,1482,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FEA4FA08F39D3CB4" box="[366,435,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1984]" captionTargetBox="[170,1422,276,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,267,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Conognatha (Pithiscus) coffeatus Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1 and 3, habitus; 2, lateral view; 4, frontal view of head; 5, ventral view of antennae; 6, shape of pronotum; 7, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224727/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FE69FA09F39D3CB4" box="[419,435,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), trapezoidal in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FDA0FA09F0DA3CB5" box="[618,756,1483,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FDA0FA09F0DA3CB5" box="[618,756,1483,1506]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FCCEFA08F17A3CB4" box="[772,852,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1430,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 8 and 10, habitus; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FCF3FA09F17A3CB4" box="[825,852,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) and of the antennae sensory fields (superficial and rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FED3FA2DF3E13F50" box="[281,463,1519,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FED3FA2DF3E13F50" box="[281,463,1519,1543]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FE2AFA2CF00A3F50" box="[480,548,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1984]" captionTargetBox="[170,1422,276,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,267,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Conognatha (Pithiscus) coffeatus Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1 and 3, habitus; 2, lateral view; 4, frontal view of head; 5, ventral view of antennae; 6, shape of pronotum; 7, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224727/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FDDFFA2CF00A3F50" box="[533,548,1518,1543]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
), deep and sub-elliptical in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FCA9FA2DF1C03F51" box="[867,1006,1519,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FCA9FA2DF1C03F51" box="[867,1006,1519,1542]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FC34FA2CF67D3F50" box="[1022,1107,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1430,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 8 and 10, habitus; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FBFEFA2DF67D3F50" box="[1076,1107,1519,1543]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
), shape of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FA87FA2CF7B23F50" box="[1357,1436,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1984]" captionTargetBox="[170,1422,276,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,267,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Conognatha (Pithiscus) coffeatus Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1 and 3, habitus; 2, lateral view; 4, frontal view of head; 5, ventral view of antennae; 6, shape of pronotum; 7, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224727/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Figs. 
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FA44FA2CF7B23F50" box="[1422,1436,1518,1543]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FF0CF9D1F2CA3F7C" box="[198,228,1555,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1430,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 8 and 10, habitus; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FF0CF9D1F2CA3F7C" box="[198,228,1555,1579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
), dimensions of scutellum (as long as wide in 
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FD24F9D1F1843F7C" box="[750,938,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FD24F9D1F1883F7C" box="[750,934,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">C. (P.) coffeatus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
wider than long in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FB4CF9D1F7213F7D" box="[1158,1295,1555,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FB4CF9D1F7213F7D" box="[1158,1295,1555,1578]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and by the pattern of punctation on elytra (
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FE30F9F5F0AD3F19" box="[506,643,1591,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FE30F9F5F0AD3F19" box="[506,643,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smaller punctures than 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FC70F9F5F6403F18" box="[954,1134,1591,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FC70F9F5F6403F18" box="[954,1134,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="507C36976451FF99FF0DF998F3773FC0" blockId="3.[151,1437,258,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FEAAF999F03D3F24" box="[352,531,1627,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FEAAF999F03D3F24" box="[352,531,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FD83F999F0FE3F25" box="[585,720,1627,1650]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FD83F999F0FE3F25" box="[585,720,1627,1650]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from each other by the shape of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FAEAF998F7433F25" box="[1312,1389,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1984]" captionTargetBox="[170,1422,276,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,267,1940]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Conognatha (Pithiscus) coffeatus Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1 and 3, habitus; 2, lateral view; 4, frontal view of head; 5, ventral view of antennae; 6, shape of pronotum; 7, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224727/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
Figs. 
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FA95F999F7433F25" box="[1375,1389,1627,1650]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="C8F82A126451FF99FF5DF9BDF29B3FC0" box="[151,181,1663,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1430,193,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 8 and 10, habitus; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FF5DF9BDF29B3FC0" box="[151,181,1663,1687]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
, respectively).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="507C36976451FF99FF0DF961F75C3E8C" blockId="3.[151,1437,258,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FF0DF961F3AE3FEC" box="[199,384,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FF0DF961F3AE3FEC" box="[199,384,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FDD5F961F1513FEC" authority="Thery, 1932" authorityName="Thery" authorityYear="1932" box="[543,895,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochereaui" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FDD5F961F0C23FEC" box="[543,748,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) rochereaui</emphasis>
Théry, 
<number id="E60B24B06451FF99FC82F961F1513FEC" box="[840,895,1699,1723]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" value="1932.0">1932</number>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="28D476076451FF99FC01F960F6153FEC" box="[971,1083,1698,1723]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, in general shape of body and general colour pattern. In contrast, they differ from each other by the colour of head, pronotum and ventral surface (black in 
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FEC0F929F3E33E54" box="[266,461,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FEC0F929F3E43E54" box="[266,458,1771,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">C. (P.) coffeatus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
dark blue in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FDBEF929F16A3E54" box="[628,836,1771,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochereaui" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FDBEF929F16A3E54" box="[628,836,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) rochereaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); lateral margin of pronotum (rectilinear in 
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FA9AF929F32C3E70" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FA9AF929F2D03E70" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">C. (P.) coffeatus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
curved in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FEBCF8CDF0143E71" box="[374,570,1806,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochereaui" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FEBCF8CDF0143E71" box="[374,570,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) rochereaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); disc of pronotum (almost flat in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FC7DF8CDF6463E70" box="[951,1128,1807,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FC7DF8CDF6463E70" box="[951,1128,1807,1831]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and convex anteriorly in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FA49F8CDF36F3E1C" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochereaui" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FA49F8CDF36F3E1C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) rochereaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pattern of striae on elytra (narrower in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FCFCF8F1F1DA3E1C" box="[822,1012,1843,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FCFCF8F1F1DA3E1C" box="[822,1012,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, wider and more evident in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FA85F8F1F3203E39" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochereaui" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FA85F8F1F3203E39" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) rochereaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), shape of basal angles of elytra (prominent and produced laterally in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FBD9F895F6EA3E38" box="[1043,1220,1879,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FBD9F895F6EA3E38" box="[1043,1220,1879,1903]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not prominent and rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FED6F8B9F3C63EC4" box="[284,488,1915,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochereaui" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FED6F8B9F3C63EC4" box="[284,488,1915,1939]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) rochereaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Furthermore, there are differences between both species in elytral colour pattern (black to dark brown with metallic reflections in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FD7EF85DF1483EE0" box="[692,870,1951,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FD7EF85DF1483EE0" box="[692,870,1951,1975]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, blue with purple reflections in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FB0DF85DF7A53EE1" box="[1223,1419,1950,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochereaui" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FB0DF85DF7A53EE1" box="[1223,1419,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) rochereaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), pattern and number of elytral bands and maculae (five pairs in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FC9EF801F6283E8C" box="[852,1030,1987,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coffeatus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FC9EF801F6283E8C" box="[852,1030,1987,2011]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) coffeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, two pairs in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146451FF99FB57F801F74C3E8C" box="[1181,1378,1987,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rochereaui" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856451FF99FB57F801F74C3E8C" box="[1181,1378,1987,2011]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="117">C. (P.) rochereaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="04BC661F6456FF9EFF5DF938F7A83E78" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224728/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" targetBox="[167,1430,207,1764]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="507C36976456FF9EFF5DF938F7A83E78" blockId="4.[151,1436,1786,1839]" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFF5DF938F3683E47" bold="true" box="[151,326,1786,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">FIGURES 8–14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146456FF9EFE86F938F1603E47" authority="Portela &amp; Mermudes" authorityName="Portela &amp; Mermudes" box="[332,846,1786,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFE86F938F0583E47" box="[332,630,1786,1808]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">Conognatha (Pithiscus) puris</emphasis>
Portela &amp; Mermudes
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="798457FE6456FF9EFC9EF938F18A3E47" box="[852,932,1786,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" rank="species">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFC9EF938F18A3E47" bold="true" box="[852,932,1786,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype male: 8 and 10, 
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFB65F938F6D43E47" box="[1199,1274,1786,1808]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">habitus</emphasis>
; 9, lateral view; 11, frontal view of head; 12, ventral view of antennae; 13, shape of pronotum; 14, dorsal view of aedeagus. Scale bar: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="507C36976456FF9FFF0DF89EF00639AF" blockId="4.[151,1436,1883,2016]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146456FF9EFF0DF89EF37F3E24" box="[199,337,1884,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFF0DF89EF37F3E24" box="[199,337,1884,1907]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146456FF9EFE03F89EF1193E23" authority="Chevrolat, 1838" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1838" box="[457,823,1883,1908]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoreyi" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFE03F89EF0493E24" box="[457,615,1883,1907]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">C. (P.) thoreyi</emphasis>
(Chevrolat, 
<number id="E60B24B06456FF9EFD3CF89EF11E3E23" box="[758,816,1884,1908]" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" value="1838.0">1838</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the general form. In contrast, they differ from each other by colour of head, pronotum and ventral surface (green to blue and brilliant in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146456FF9EFB98F842F6DE3EC0" box="[1106,1264,1919,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoreyi" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFB98F842F6DE3EC0" box="[1106,1264,1919,1943]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">C. (P.) thoreyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and black and matt in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146456FF9EFF26F866F35B3EEC" box="[236,373,1956,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFF26F866F35B3EEC" box="[236,373,1956,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); presence of a short longitudinal groove between the vertex and the frons in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146456FF9EFB12F866F74E3EEC" box="[1240,1376,1956,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFB12F866F74E3EEC" box="[1240,1376,1956,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; disc of pronotum (convex in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146456FF9EFE6DF80AF06A3E88" box="[423,580,1991,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoreyi" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFE6DF80AF06A3E88" box="[423,580,1991,2015]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">C. (P.) thoreyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and almost flattened in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146456FF9EFC99F80AF1F23E88" box="[851,988,1992,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856456FF9EFC99F80AF1F23E88" box="[851,988,1992,2015]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="118">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Additionally, the new species have no fovea on the basal angles of pronotum nor pre-scutellary impression (both present in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146457FF9FFB99FF5AF6DE39E7" box="[1107,1264,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoreyi" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856457FF9FFB99FF5AF6DE39E7" box="[1107,1264,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">C. (P.) thoreyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and they also differ from each other by the elytral colour pattern and the form of punctured striae (well marked along the entire length of the elytra in 
<taxonomicName id="97C34D146457FF9FFE45FF22F03939A0" box="[399,535,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puris" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="62B7EA856457FF9FFE45FF22F03939A0" box="[399,535,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="119">C. (P.) puris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
